SIMPLE: forester
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forester
<hw>For"est*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>forestier</ets>, LL. <ets>forestarius</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who has charge of the growing timber on an estate; an officer
appointed to watch a forest and preserve the game.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An inhabitant of a forest.</def>
<rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A forest tree.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A lepidopterous insect belonging
to <gen>Alypia</gen> and allied genera; <as>as, the eight-spotted
<ex>forester</ex> (<spn>A. octomaculata</spn>), which in the larval
state is injurious to the grapevine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forestick</ent>⟦br⟧
